  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nThe [`integer_squareroot`](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#integer_squareroot) function could be logically equal to `math.floor(math.sqrt(value))`.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\nI simply tried to use `math.floor(math.sqrt(value))`. However, it didn't pass the test case of big number:\r\n```\r\nactual     = 4294967296\r\nexpected   = 4294967295\r\nvalue      = 18446744073709551615\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe can investigate it later.",
