    "body": "This works:\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef fast_integer_sqrt(value: int) -> int:\r\n    with decimal.localcontext() as ctx:\r\n        ctx.prec = 100\r\n        return int(decimal.Decimal(value).sqrt())\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like it's about 4x faster as profiled using:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport random\r\nimport timeit\r\n\r\ndef integer_sqrt(value: int) -> int:\r\n    ...\r\n\r\ndef fast_integer_sqrt(value: int) -> int:\r\n    ...\r\n\r\ndef test_time_base():\r\n    print('base', timeit.timeit(\"integer_sqrt(random.randint(0, 2**256 - 1))\", globals={\"integer_sqrt\": integer_sqrt, 'random': random}))\r\n\r\ndef test_time_fast():\r\n    print('fast', timeit.timeit(\"fast_integer_sqrt(random.randint(0, 2**256 - 1))\", globals={\"fast_integer_sqrt\": fast_integer_sqrt, 'random': random}))\r\n```",
