    "body": "@pipermerriam \r\n\r\n> You might experiment with the precision as 100 was chosen arbitrarily and is likely overkill though i don't know how much it will effect performance.\r\n\r\nTheoretically speaking, the largest square root of a 256 bit integer is a 128 bit integer. I, therefore, think that the `ctx.prec` should be set to `128`.\r\n\r\nI've also been comparing different implementations for finding integer square roots ([ref](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15390807/integer-square-root-in-python)), and the one suggested by you turns out to be the fastest. Would you like me to submit a PR?",
